22 Section 5. Designation of the State from Which Licensee is Applying for a Compact
23 Privilege
24 A. Upon a Licensee’s application for a Compact Privilege, the Licensee shall identify
25 to the Commission the Participating State from which the Licensee is applying, in
26 accordance with applicable Rules adopted by the Commission, and subject to the
27 following requirements:
28 1. When applying for a Compact Privilege, the Licensee shall provide the
29 Commission with the address of the Licensee’s primary residence and
30 thereafter shall immediately report to the Commission any change in the
31 address of the Licensee’s primary residence.
32 2. When applying for a Compact Privilege, the Licensee is required to consent
33 to accept service of process by mail at the Licensee’s primary residence on
34 file with the Commission with respect to any action brought against the
35 Licensee by the Commission or a Participating State, including a subpoena,
